To filter an array of strings based on a minimum length requirement in JavaScript, you can use the `filter` method. This method creates a new array with all elements that pass the test implemented by the provided function. Here's how you can do it:

```javascript
function filterByMinLength(stringsArray, minLength) {
  return stringsArray.filter(function(string) {
    return string.length >= minLength;
  });
}

// Example usage:
const stringsArray = ["apple", "banana", "pear", "grape", "kiwi"];
const minLength = 5;
const filteredArray = filterByMinLength(stringsArray, minLength);

console.log(filteredArray); // Output: ["apple", "banana", "grape"]
```

In this example, the `filterByMinLength` function takes an array of strings and a minimum length as parameters, then returns a new array containing only the strings that have a length greater than or equal to the specified minimum length.
